'''CohnReznick LLP''' is a national [[professional services]] firm headquartered in New York, NY. It is the eleventh largest public accounting firm in the United States based on aggregated 2017 revenues.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://editiondigital.net/publication/?i=479119&ver=html5&p=1|title=2018 Top 100 Firms and Regional Leaders|last=|first=|date=|work=Accounting Today|access-date=2018-03-20|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en}}</ref>
The Firm’s services are aligned in three segments: accounting, tax, and advisory. It has 26 offices, over 2,600 employees (as of 2017), and reported annual revenue of $625 million (for fiscal year ending 1/31/18).<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cohnreznick.com/offices|title=Office Locator|website=www.cohnreznick.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref> CohnReznick was formed in 2012 through a combination of two firms: J.H. Cohn (Roseland, NJ) and Reznick Group (Bethesda, MD).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cohnreznick.com/about|title=About|website=www.cohnreznick.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref> J.H. Cohn was founded in 1919 in Newark, NJ by Julius H. Cohn. Reznick Group, formerly Reznick, Fedder & Silverman, was formed in 1977 in Washington, DC by three partners – David Reznick, Stuart Fedder, and Ivan Silverman.
== International == CohnReznick is a member of Nexia International,<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://nexia.com|title=Home|website=nexia.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref>{{fv|date=March 2018|reason=Not in citatoin given. Perhaps a more specific reference was intended}} a worldwide network of independent [[Accounting networks and associations|accounting and consulting firms]]. The Nexia network includes more than 23,000 professionals operating in over 100 countries.<ref name=":1" />
